ROUND 4: KEYSTORE LOSS, STORAGE LOCK, AND CHAT RECOVERY DESIGN

This round is design only. Do not edit code, create migrations, add UI, or commit changes.

Verified problem:

Chat history is stored through SecurePrefs and Android Keystore-backed encryption. If the key becomes unavailable or encrypted data cannot be decrypted, the current fallback can make chats appear empty. The app may then accept writes into plaintext or fallback storage. If encryption later becomes available, migration rules may prefer the older encrypted copy and silently discard data written during the outage.

The memory database already has an explicit locked-store concept. Chat history does not have an equivalent reliable storage state.

The goal is to design a recovery-safe storage state machine that never presents unreadable encrypted data as ordinary empty data and never silently deletes either side of an encrypted/plaintext conflict.

